<h2>
    <strong>Fishing Regulations and Licensing in Oregon</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Before casting a line, every angler needs to understand the rules:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>License Requirements</strong>: Anyone 12 years or older must have a valid Oregon fishing license and a Combined Angling Tag to harvest steelhead.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Harvest Limits</strong>: Typically, you can keep one hatchery steelhead per day, up to a certain limit. Wild steelhead must be released.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Special Rules</strong>: Some rivers have seasonal closures, gear restrictions, or barbless hook requirements.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Always check the Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife for the most current regulations.
</p>
