<h2>
    <strong>Effective Fishing Techniques for Steelhead</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Steelhead are notoriously tough to catch, but with the right approach, your odds increase:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Drift Fishing</strong>: Cast upriver with natural baits like roe or nightcrawlers and let the current do the work.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Fly Fishing</strong>: Using nymphs, streamers, or dry flies in shallower sections can be effective during low-light periods.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Hardware Tactics</strong>: Spinners and spoons in silver or chartreuse are effective, especially after a light rain when visibility is lower.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Adjust your tactics based on water clarity and flow rate for best results.
</p>
