<h2>
    <strong>Tips for Catch and Release Fishing</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Practicing ethical catch and release is essential for preserving steelhead populations, especially wild fish. Here’s how to do it right:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Use Barbless Hooks</strong>: Makes unhooking easier and causes less damage.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Keep Fish Wet</strong>: Avoid lifting fish out of water for more than a few seconds.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Use Rubber Nets</strong>: They are less abrasive on fish scales and slime coating.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Handle Gently</strong>: Wet your hands before touching fish; avoid squeezing.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Revive Before Release</strong>: Hold the fish facing upstream until it swims off strongly.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Following these tips ensures fish survive to complete their spawning journey.
